References:-
https://www.ibm.com/support/pages/node/7263725 

I have used 2 ec2 instances. One for Nomad server and other for Nomad client.

Steps:-
----------------- On Nomad Server ---------
Deploy Nomad server on ec2 instance using nomad-server.hcl
Verify that Prometheus metrics are exposed: curl http://localhost:4646/v1/metrics
Deploy Prometheus server on same ec2 instance (Nomad server).[I have used same ec2 instance, however we can use a different one as well]
cd /opt
sudo wget https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/releases/download/v3.9.1/prometheus-3.9.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz
sudo tar xvf prometheus-3.9.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz
sudo mv prometheus-3.9.1.linux-amd64 prometheus
sudo vi /opt/prometheus/prometheus.yml   (refer prometheus.yml attached in this directory)
cd /opt/prometheus
Run the prometheus server:-
nohup ./prometheus --config.file=prometheus.yml --web.listen-address="0.0.0.0:9090" &
Open the Prometheus UI in a browser: http://<SERVER_PUBLIC_IP>:9090
Navigate to Status → Target Health (You may also search In the query box, try: {job="nomad"} or {exported_job="hello-world"})

----------------- On Nomad Client ---------
Deploy Nomad client on ec2 instance using nomad-client.hcl
Install and Deploy nomad-autoscaler-enterprise:0.4.9-ent on the Nomad client, steps given below:-
wget https://releases.hashicorp.com/nomad-autoscaler/0.4.9+ent/nomad-autoscaler_0.4.9+ent_linux_amd64.zip
unzip nomad-autoscaler_0.4.9+ent_linux_amd64.zip
mv nomad-autoscaler /usr/local/bin/
nomad-autoscaler version
Start the nomad-autoscaler: "nohup nomad-autoscaler agent -config=autoscaler.hcl -enable-debug &"
Run the Nomad job:
nomad job run hello-world-DAS-job.hcl   # For DAS i.e Dynamic application scaling. On the Nomad UI -> Optimize -> You will see the recommendations for the job. If you accept it the job will be restarted with the recommended resources
nomad job run hello-world-horizontal-app-scaling-job.hcl   # For horizontal application scaling


